Ex. No: 11 — Handling Missing Data using fillna(), dropna(), and Interpolation
Aim
To identify and handle missing data using Pandas functions.
Theory
Missing values affect data analysis.
Pandas provides functions like fillna(), dropna(), and interpolate() to handle missing data.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library

program
import pandas as pd

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'Student': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya', 'Arun'],
    'Marks': [85, None, 90, None, 88]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Original DataFrame:")
print(df)

# Missing values
print("\nMissing Values:")
print(df.isna())

# fillna()
print("\nAfter fillna():")
print(df.fillna(0))

# dropna()
print("\nAfter dropna():")
print(df.dropna())

# interpolation
print("\nAfter Interpolation:")
print(df.interpolate())

Procedure


Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Pandas library.
Create DataFrame with missing values.
Display original dataset.
Identify missing values using isna()
Replace missing values using fillna().
Remove missing rows using dropna().
Apply interpolation.
